theorem
  f is_strictly_convex_on X iff X c= dom f & for a,b,r st a in X & b in
X & r in X & a < r & r < b holds (f.r-f.a)/(r-a) < (f.b-f.a)/(b-a) & (f.b-f.a)/
  (b-a) < (f.b-f.r)/(b-r)
proof
A1: X c= dom f & (for a,b,r st a in X & b in X & r in X & a < r & r < b
